<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 18 at 3:42AM EDT  by NWS NorthernIndiana</headline>
<description>...AREAS OF LOW LYING FOG THIS MORNING WITH PATCHY DENSE FOG...
Expect areas if low lying fog this morning, with patches of dense
fog possible. If travelling, be alert for sudden reductions in
visibility. Visibilities could linger around 1 mile for many
locations, but in denser fog it could drop to less than one half
of a mile. If dense fog is encountered, use your low beams, reduce
speed, and increase following distance. Fog should begin to
diminish shortly after sunrise.</description>
